
title: PowerShell Spawning CScript for VBS Execution
id: 2c7d6a5a-6f6f-4a4c-9b1d-9e5dbe4d7c21
status: experimental
author: Busra Ugur
date: 2026-01-29
description: >
  Detects PowerShell spawning cscript.exe to execute a Visual Basic Script (.vbs).
  This behavior is commonly associated with scripted execution chains used in
  living-off-the-land attacks, fileless malware delivery, and adversary automation.

references:
  - https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/005/

logsource:
  product: windows
  category: process_creation

detection:
  selection:
    Image|endswith: '\cscript.exe'
    ParentImage|endswith: '\powershell.exe'
    CommandLine|contains: '.vbs'

  condition: selection

falsepositives:
  - Legitimate administrative scripting activity
  - Enterprise automation or software deployment tools
  - Developer testing or red team simulations

level: medium

tags:
  - attack.execution
  - attack.t1059.005
  - attack.lolbin
